<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Travailer" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Travailer</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Travailor</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Traveiler</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Travellour</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Traveller</orth> (the last form alone used by M. Edd.), 1) a labourer: <cit><quote>as fast locked up in sleep as guiltless labour when it lies starkly in the --'s bones,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 70</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>as motion and long-during action tires the sinewy vigour of the t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.308" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 308</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) one who goes a journey, a wayfarer: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 1, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.4.18" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 4, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.5.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 5, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 2, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 3, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 1, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 139</bibl> (Qq <emph>travels</emph>). <bibl n="shak. cym 1.4.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 4, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.123" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 2, 123</bibl>.
<lb />3) one who has seen foreign countries: <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 3, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.164" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.97" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 1, 21</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.277" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 277</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.5.30" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.189" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 189</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>